class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        // Find the highest power of three that fits in the given number
        int highestPowerOfThree = 1;
        while (highestPowerOfThree < n) {
            highestPowerOfThree = highestPowerOfThree * 3;
        }

        return n == highestPowerOfThree;
    }
}
```
This solution uses a simple approach. We first find the highest power of three that fits in the given number by multiplying it by 3 repeatedly. Then, we check if the given number is equal to this highest power of three.

The time complexity of this solution is O(log3(n)), where n is the given number.

